qas.question: What was the capital of Burma?
What was the principle port of Burma?
What force was delayed by Japanese rearguards north of Rangoon?

context: During <a4_0>April<a4_0/>, <a3_0>Fourteenth Army<a3_0/> advanced 300 miles (480 km) south towards <a0_0><a1_0>Rangoon<a1_0/><a0_0/>, the capital and principal port of Burma, but was delayed by Japanese rearguards 40 miles (64 km) north of Rangoon at the end of the month. Slim feared that the Japanese would defend Rangoon house-to-house during the monsoon, placing his army in a disastrous supply situation, and in March he had asked that a plan to capture Rangoon by an amphibious force, Operation Dracula, which had been abandoned earlier, be reinstated. Dracula was launched on <a2_0>1 May<a2_0/>, but Rangoon was found to have been abandoned. The troops which occupied Rangoon linked up with Fourteenth Army five days later, securing the Allies' lines of communication.
